# PII and personal sensitive content -- never commit to public repo

## Hard rule (enforced on every session, every file, every commit)

The following categories of information **MUST NEVER** appear in any file that is
tracked by the **public Git** (`origin` / GitHub). They belong **exclusively** in:
- `docs/private/` (gitignored from public; has its own stacked private git)
- Session memory (chat only, not persisted to tracked files)
- Password manager / secure vault

---

## Categories of information that are PRIVATE-ONLY

### 1. Operator identity and family
- Full legal name of the operator or any family member (spouse, children, parents, siblings)
- CPF, RG, or any national ID number (pattern: `\d{3}\.\d{3}\.\d{3}-\d{2}` or 11 bare digits)
- Physical address, neighborhood, city/state beyond "Rio de Janeiro" as region
- Date of birth of operator or family
- Wedding anniversary date or family event dates
- Spouse employer, workplace, or detailed career info
- Any reference to children, godparents, wedding witnesses by full name + role

### 2. Employment and career
- Full name of current or past **employer** (replace with "the operator employer", "a port logistics company", etc. in public docs)
- Specific job title + company combination that uniquely identifies the operator
- Salary, compensation, or benefit details
- Details of employment disputes (dossier content -- keep in docs/private/ only)
- Reference letters, demission interviews, HR correspondence

### 3. Financial information
- Personal income, bank account, FGTS balance
- OPEX/CAPEX amounts for household or lab-op
- Shopping lists with prices for personal use
- Subscription costs, utility bill amounts
- Pricing studies and commercial proposals (also covered by confidential-commercial-never-tracked.mdc)

### 4. Health and medical
- Diagnoses, medications, psychiatrist/psychologist notes
- Medical letters or correspondence
- Burnout, CID, INSS/CAT documents
- Weight, surgical history, or other medical details

### 5. Lab-op infrastructure
- Real hostnames (use lab-pb, lab-op or <hostname> placeholders in public docs)
- LAN IP addresses (RFC1918: 192.168.x.x, 10.x.x.x, 172.16-31.x.x)
- Hardware serial numbers, MAC addresses
- SSH private keys, API tokens, passwords, SNMP communities
- UDM/UniFi client MAC lists or device fingerprints with real names

### 6. Feedback and external reviews (MUST be in private git -- NOT gitignored from it)
- Wabbix, Gemini, or partner review reports -- docs/private/feedbacks_and_reviews/
- These are evidence and MUST be committed to the stacked private git
- Raw Gemini chat dumps, Gemini bundles -- docs/private/gemini_bundles/
- The gitignored "docs/feedbacks, reviews, comments and criticism/" is a working inbox only
  Mirror all receipts to docs/private/feedbacks_and_reviews/ and commit to private git

### 7. Courses, certifications, study enrollment
- Specific course enrollment status, fee paid, platform login
- Detailed study schedule tied to personal calendar
- Academic transcripts, grades, thesis drafts -- docs/private/author_info/

### 8. Personal legal matters
- Labor dispute dossier (any employer) -- keep in docs/private/ only
- Any document that is "privileged" (attorney-client, court filing, settlement)
- Third-party names in legal context (except genericized references)

---

## What IS acceptable in public tracked files

- Author name in LICENSE, NOTICE, README (standard FOSS practice -- single canonical occurrence)
- Genericized references: "the operator", "the operator employer", "a port terminal operator"
- ADRs that describe decisions without naming real companies or people
- Plans and to-dos without financial figures or personal identifiers
- Wabbix/Gemini analysis summaries in docs/plans/WABBIX_ANALISE_*.md when they contain
  only product-level recommendations (no personal data, no vulnerability exploitation details)
- Process docs (docs/ops/) describing how to send/receive reviews (no real content inside)

---

## Audience tiers (see audience-segmentation-docs.mdc)

| Tier | Path | Allowed to contain PII? |
|---|---|---|
| External / GitHub public | docs/, tracked *.md, scripts/, .cursor/ | NO -- stub/generic only |
| Internal project | docs/plans/, docs/ops/, docs/adr/ | No personal PII; product/process only |
| Secrets-access | docs/private/ (gitignored + stacked private git) | YES -- full context |

---

## Agent actions on violation

1. **Stop and flag** before committing: if a file about to be staged contains PII from the
   categories above, do NOT commit it -- move to docs/private/ first.
2. **Replace** with generic wording in the public file and document the real detail in the
   matching docs/private/ companion.
3. **Scan before PR**: look for patterns in the diff: 11-digit sequences (CPF),
   full names of family members, RFC1918 IPs, real employer names.
4. **Private git commit --trailer "Made-with: Cursor"**: after any session that adds content to docs/private/,
   run scripts/private-git-sync.ps1 or git -C docs/private add -A && commit.

---

## Stacked private repo commit cadence

- Commit after every meaningful session that changes private files
- Use chore(private): prefix in commit messages
- Push to lab-latitude/main regularly (pCloud P:/ is additional backup, not sole copy)
- feedbacks_and_reviews/ must be committed -- never gitignored from the private repo

See docs/private/ for full private git workflow.
